author: (Pat Evans)
title: Bank expands its reach
text:
United Bank will renovate a former eye doctor's office in Jenison into a branch. Photo via fb.com 
A West Michigan-based bank is growing its presence in a Grand Rapids suburb. 
United Bank recently purchased the former Georgetown Eye Associates office at 1884 Baldwin St. in Jenison. 
The bank will renovate the 4,040-square-foot building for use as a branch office. The optometry office will open a new office in February 2016. 
Kurt Kunst of NAI Wisinski of West Michigan represented United Bank , while Al Rietberg of Rietberg Companies represented the seller. 
The new branch will be Unitedâ€™s westernmost location in the region. United currently has offices in Byron Center, Caledonia, Cascade, Dorr, East Grand Rapids, southeast Grand Rapids, Hopkins, Rockford and Wayland.
